#Above information shows that there is no missing value (NaN) in the dataset. But when we check the csv file many attributes like Glucose, BP, SkinThickness, Insulin and BMI has zero values which is not possible for a normal human being. So we can consider these zero values as invalid values similar as NaN
#Also from the above information we could see that our target variable "Outcome" is defined as an integer data type. For our analysis purpose lets consider it as a categorical variable (0 - Nondiabetic / 1 - Diabetic) by changing its dtype
In [10]:

In [28]:
def draw_boxplot(df, X, xlab, title):

    x           =   df[X]
    Outcome     =   df['Outcome']
    
    print("\n summary for Outcome vs " + xlab + "\n")
    print(df[X].groupby(df['Outcome']).describe().T)

    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x = df[X] ,y = df['Outcome'])
    ax.set_title(title)
    plt.show()
